data.description: This single-family home is ideally located in a peaceful neighborhood, offering the best of both worlds -- a tranquil retreat and easy access to nearby amenities, schools, and recreational facilities. The home has had its garage converted to include 2 additional bedrooms, a second kitchen, and extra living space. Each section of this home has its own entry and side yard. From the front yard you can see Mount San Jacinto perfectly. Whether you have a large family or wish to have room mates, this home has a layout that will accommodate everyone's desired comfort and space. The owners have recently painted the main living area, creating a bright and inviting atmosphere. The floors are currently exposed concrete, providing a blank canvas for your personal touch. If you wish to install new flooring, half the work is already done!Embrace eco-friendly living with solar panels adorning the roof, harnessing the power of the sun to provide energy for your home, reducing your carbon footprint and energy costs.Don't miss the chance to make this spacious and versatile home your own! Schedule a viewing today to explore the possibilities and envision the lifestyle awaiting you.
